{"id": "duc04-testb-13:3#10", "contents": "Thai Deputy Prime Minister Bhichai Rattakul, also chairman of the Thai organizing committee, welcomed the delegation and addressed their concerns. He acknowledged that the country had faced difficulties in its preparations, largely due to the financial crisis, but assured the delegates that Thailand had made every effort to accommodate their requests. Bhichai emphasized that the successful preparation of the games despite the challenges was a testament to Asia's resiliency. Manuel Veguillas, head of the Philippine delegation, echoed this sentiment, stating that \"this is an example of Asia's resiliency\" and expressing his impression with the preparations."}
